==English==
===Noun===
'''tangent''', ''plural'' '''tangents'''

#(''geometry'') A [[straight]] [[line]] [[touching]] a [[curve]] at a single [[point]] without [[crossing]] it there.
#(''trigonometry'') In a [[right triangle]], the [[ratio]] of the [[length]] of the [[side]] [[opposite]] the [[angle]] to the length of the side [[adjacent]] to the angle.
#{{mathematics}} The ratio of the [[sine]] to the [[cosine]], in either the [[real]] or [[complex]] [[number]]s.
#A [[topic]] nearly [[unrelated]] to the main topic, but having a point in [[common]] with it.
#: ''I believe we got off onto a tangent when we started talking about unicycles.''

